title: Rare John Lennnon - The Absolute Madman
description:
This album was inspired by the well-known viral photo of John doing a silly walk. It contains some rare and not-so-rare recordings from The Beatles-era. 

01. Madman (1969 outtake)
02. Can He Walk? (1969 outtake)
03. Slow Down (BBC, 1963)
04. I've Got A Woman, We Crossed Town (BBC, 1963)
05. When The Saints Go Marching In (with Tony Sheridan, 1961)
06. The One After 909 (1963 outtake)
07. Come Together (1969 outtake)
08. I Want You (She's So Heavy) (1969 outtake)
09. Lady Madonna (2009 version)
10. I Am The Walrus (2009 version)
11. Your Feets Too Big (live 1962)
12. Studio Fails / Working Class Hero (bonus track)
